This solution works by repeatedly dividing the input number `n` by 3 as long as it is divisible by 3. This effectively removes factors of 3 from `n` until it is reduced to a single 3^x, where x is an integer. If `n` is 1 at the end, then it was originally a power of 3.

However, this solution does use a loop, which doesn't meet the "without loops/recursion" requirement. We can use a different approach using logarithms:

